   212	                THE CLEVELAND FREE-NET COMPUTER COMPLEX:
   213	
   214	   The Cleveland Free-Net is not a single computer.  It is a collection
   215	of more than a dozen machines all operating in coordination with
   216	each other, and all maintained on the campus of Case Western Reserve
   217	University by CWRU's Information Network Services group.
   218	
   219	   At the heart of the system are machines from several different vendors.
   220	These machines have been linked together via an ethernet connection
   221	so that, from the users standpoint, they appear as one large machine.
   222	
   223	   Access to the Free-Net is provided via three methods.  The first 
   224	is via asynchronous modem where phone lines are available for 
   225	community access.  More phone lines and modems may be added as
   226	community demand increases. The second method is via both the
   227	fiber-optic lines and modems of CWRUnet, the university's new
   228	campus information network.
   229	
   230	   The Free-Net is also available to users around the world via the
   231	university's connection to the Internet.  The Internet is a collection
   232	of thousands of computer systems located in almost every part of the
   233	world.
